name: Blingineering
description:
In August 2003, HP released the 49g+. This unit had metallic gold coloration and was backward compatible with the HP 49G. Instead of the rubber keyboard found on the HP 49G, this calculator's keyboard had plastic hinges intended to return the feel of older HP calculators, and also included a pouch to protect the unit, similar to those included with older HP models.

This calculator featured an entirely new processor architecture, USB and IrDA (infrared) communication, memory expansion via an SD card, and a slightly larger screen, as well as other improvements over the previous model.

name: These objects are NOT to scale...
description: Let this be a warning to you: these objects are not to scale! If you use them to measure or protract, you are inviting disaster. Removing your shirt during an exam is frowned upon by the faculty, even if you are just trying to draw a right angle. Light blue print on AmericanApparel creme tee.

name: Stormtrooper?
description: Stormtrooper? No, no, no, good sir. Make no mistake; this is the helmet of a Squall Squadroneer, and not a Stormtrooper. You see Squall Squadroneers are plaid, wheras Stormtroopers are white, which is obviously totally different. Slightly less obvious is the fact that Stomtroopers are the intellecual property of Lucasarts, and Squall Squadroneers are a completely unique concept that don't infringe on any existing trademarks. Grey and aqua on an AmericanApparel sunshine tee.

name: Yellow/Aqua Logo Shirt
description: Tired of being unable to manipulate numbers? Then this is your lucky day, friend! Wearing this shirt will confer you with the power to add and subtract quantities! It has been said that you can even perform these operations iteratively to unlock the mysteries of multiplication and division. Yellow watercolour print on AmericanApparel aqua tee.
